    ],
    "summary": "On September 19, 2017 at approximately 1600 hours, a gas release occurred from a corroded 2-inch pipe containing approximately 1000 lbs of pressure. A corrosion inspector conducting annual metal integrity inspection raised the pipe off an I-beam support, causing gas to escape from a small pinhole. The inspector's personal gas monitor detected the gas. Manual ESD and muster alarm were initiated. No injuries or pollution events resulted.",
